    <sampling_method>Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Admission to hospital with suspected index event of Non-ST-Elevation Myocardial
             Infarction (NSTEMI), Unstable Angina (UA) or Stable Angina (SA)

          -  Planned percutaneous coronary intervention during admission

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Recent history (&lt; 6 months) of an acute coronary syndrome (other than current
             admission) or stroke

          -  Recent history (&lt; 6 months) of major surgery, trauma or thromboembolic event

          -  Percutaneous coronary or peripheral intervention or any stent placement performed
             within the past 6 months

          -  Current evidence of infection
      </textblock>
